description.narrative: UNICEF's collective efforts across the Health, Nutrition, WASH, and HIV/AIDS sectors served to strengthen integrated programme coordination, advocacy, evidence generation, as well as policy, strategy, and guideline development to create an enhanced enabling environment for integrated programming across the four sectors. This resulted in finalization of the Kenya Nutrition Action Plan (2018-2022) and roll out of Guidelines on Use of Antiretroviral Drugs for Treating and Preventing HIV Infection in Kenya (2018), the establishment of functional WASH coordination mechanisms across 13 counties, and 97% of health services delivery points submitting Health Management Information System (HMIS) reports. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
